# Introduction to this module

We'll begin by discussion how this seminar module will run, including what is expected of you as an effective, supportive, engaged learner.

We'll discuss how to get the most out of this course, and how you will be assessed.

We'll also discuss how you will support each other throughout the course, as well as how I can support you, as module lead.

Please take a look at the [handbook tab](Handbook.html) for further information.

### Guided discussion questions:

-   How can we discuss difficult or contentious issues openly, while accepting and respecting differences of opinion?
-   How can we explore and challenge the views of others in an intelligent, kind and sensitive way?

