# The history of women's mental health

[**Required Reading:** Simon M (2014) Fantastically Wrong: The Theory of the Wandering Wombs That Drove Women to Madness](https://www.wired.com/2014/05/fantastically-wrong-wandering-womb/){style="color:#cd5b45"}

[**Required Reading:** Cherry K (2022) Freud's Perspective on Women](https://www.verywellmind.com/how-sigmund-freud-viewed-women-2795859){style="color:#cd5b45"}

[**Optional Reading:** Libbon (2007) Pathologizing the female body: phallocentricism in Western science](https://vc.bridgew.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1401&context=jiws){style="color:#45B7CD"}

### Guided discussion questions:

- Did anything shock you about how women's psychology and mental health has been considered historically?
- Do you think these perspectives have had any impact on how women's mental health is considered today?

